Theme code
----------

`beamerthemeapographpolito.sty` and `apograph-polito-colors.sty` are
modified descendants of the SINTEF/Sapienza Beamer theme. The file-level base
used for comparison is:

  Andrea Gasparini, sapienza-beamer-template
  commit 24651c2ec532eb88544056c9b8130b7907fb553c (2022-12-09)
  https://github.com/andrea-gasparini/sapienza-beamer-template

That repository identifies the code as GPL version 3. The inherited file
header identifies Federico Zenith as the original author and Håvard Berland's
beamerthementnu as an earlier ancestor. Mattia Ippoliti adapted the work for
Politecnico di Torino. The current Apograph files are distributed under
GPL-3.0-or-later; the complete text is in `LICENSES/GPL-3.0-or-later.txt`.

Apograph modifications include package/path normalization, optional behavior,
namespaced public commands, a separate starter/config/showcase structure, a
single-file adaptation of the original teaching deck, user-provided-asset
fallbacks, reproducible artifact packaging, and current documentation. These
modifications were made by Elia Innocenti in 2026.

