Institution assets
------------------

PoliTo logos and backgrounds are not included. They are cataloged as optional
user-provided files because copyright, redistribution, and trademark evidence
has not been established. The template compiles without them. Supplying a file
locally does not change the license of that file and does not imply permission
to redistribute or use an institution mark.

PoliTo's published student guidance says that enrolled users can obtain the
title-page template and logo from the private Teaching Portal and may use the
logo for academic purposes. PoliTo's public corporate-image policy separately
states that third-party logo use requires authorization. The README points to
both sources and records the five expected destination paths. Mattia Ippoliti's
public Overleaf project is cited as the source of the original layout and
filenames, not as proof of permission to use or redistribute PoliTo marks.
